title: eleanor_hume
body:
[[Tales of Berseria]] character. An exorcist for the Abbey who is forced to accompany [[velvet crowe|Velvet]] and her party. Eleanor is reluctant to go with Velvet due to her nature as a killer, but once she sees the truth that the Abbey is hiding, she stays with the party of her own free will. Her seiyuu is [[Koshimizu Ami]].

h4.Costume Titles

* [[eleanor hume (christmas)|Christmas]]

title: magilou_(tales)
body:
[[Tales of Berseria]] character. A witch who tags along with [[velvet crowe|Velvet]] for her own goals, eventually joining the party simply because she's bored. [[bienfu (tales)|Bienfu]] is her Normin partner. Magilou's mannerisms are both bizarre and apathetic, covering up her emotions with obnoxious jokes and unusual responses to questions. Her seiyuu is [[Satou Satomi]].

title: me!me!me!
body:
Animation music video by TeddyLoid x [[daoko]] x Studio khara. The third animated short film of the [[Japan Animator Expo]].

The [[ME!ME!ME! dance (meme)|]] regained popularity in 2021, when an animation of [[Zero Two (darling in the franxx)|]] performing it went viral on TikTok. This second wind set the dance to a different song ("2 Phut Hon (KAIZ Remix)":[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yoZy2E17-50]), and is often referred to as the "Hip Sway Dance" when parodied.

title: kyou_en_(masterwork_apocalypse)
body:
Character from [[Masterwork Apocalypse]].

[b]Origin:[/b] The Investiture of the Gods, a 16th-century Chinese novel and one of the major vernacular Chinese works in the gods-and-demons (shenmo) genre written during the Ming dynasty (1368–1644). The story is set in the era of the decline of the Shang dynasty (1600–1046 BC) and the rise of the Zhou dynasty (1046–256 BC). It intertwines numerous elements of Chinese mythology, including deities, immortals and spirits. The authorship is attributed to Xu Zhonglin.

[b]Japanese voice actress:[/b] [[Taketatsu Ayana]].

title: raven_(tales)
body:
One of the cast of playable characters in Namco Bandai's [[Tales of Vesperia]]. 

Raven, [spoilers]birth-named Damuron Atomais (ダミュロン・アトマイス), then renamed [[Schwann Oltorain]]  (シュヴァーン・オルトレイン)[/spoilers], is a frivolous and shady-looking man that wears a long purple coat with light, blue-green eyes and unkempt grayish-brown hair tied up in a ponytail. Despite his fishy appearance, he is a high-ranked member of Altosk, one of the five master guilds of the Union. When his hair is down, it falls into long, uneven bangs that cover most of his left eye. 

h4.Costume Titles

* [[raven (faux gentleman) (tales)|Faux Gentleman]]
* [[raven (gentleman) (tales)|Gentleman]]
* [[raven (glorious shadow) (tales)|Glorious Shadow]]

* [[raven (notorious teacher) (tales)|Notorious Teacher]]
* [[raven (spa manager) (tales)|Spa Manager]]
* [[raven (that summer guy) (tales)|That Summer Guy]]

title: flynn_scifo
body:
Flynn Scifo  is a major character from [i][[Tales of Vesperia]][/i]. He is [[Yuri Lowell]]'s best friend, though they do not show it much. He is a part of the Imperial Knights and, unlike Yuri, he wishes to change the empire from the inside. He is often accompanied by [[Witcher (tales)|]] and [[Sodia (tales)|]]. He is only playable for one fight in the XBox version, but becomes a permanent party member in the PS3 version.

title: judith_(tales)
body:
Judith is a playable character in [[Tales of Vesperia]] who wields a spear. She is a member of the Kritya tribe, a minority race. 

She appears to be one of the more mysterious, mature and rational members of the team. She is decisive, persistent, witty, somewhat impulsive, and quite bold, apparently preferring to wear several revealing outfits, particularly her default outfit and her bunny outfit. 

She is also very flirtatious and apparently enjoys teasing the male members of the team, especially [[Raven (tales)|]] and [[Karol Capel|Karol]], and often makes suggestive comments about 'showing a little more' of her already-impressive figure. [[estellise sidos heurassein|Estelle]] has humorously shown to be jealous of it. She has also stated that she is "not a very good liar".

title: karol_capel
body:
Karol Capel is a party member from [[Tales of Vesperia]]. A young boy who wields a giant hammer and various other large weapons. Having grown up in Dahngrest, the home to many of the world's Guilds, Karol knows a lot about the functioning and culture of Guilds. Despite the fact that he acts with a lot of bravado, Karol lacks self-confidence, which leaves him rather cowardly in terms of actions. Due to this cowardice, Karol is repeatedly mocked in Dahngrest for joining and being kicked out of many different Guilds.

title: estellise_sidos_heurassein
body:
Estellise Sidos Heurassein, better known as Estelle, is the main female lead in [[Tales of Vesperia]]. 

Estelle is an 18 year old noblewoman who has spent all of her life growing up in Zaphias Castle. Due to her restrictive upbringing, she has gained most of her worldly knowledge through books. Despite her abundance of trivial knowledge, she has never left the castle and is sorely lacking in real-world experience. This becomes evident in her difficulty making critical decisions. Good-natured and selfless, she often puts others before herself.

title: yuri_lowell
body:
The main character of [[Tales of Vesperia]], the tenth major release in the [[tales_of_(series)|Tales Series]]. A young man from the imperial capital, Zaphias, Yuri is forced to leave his life in the Lower Quarter behind to pursue the thief who stole the blastia core required for regulating the area's water supply. His pursuit of the thief eventually leads to him being imprisoned in the castle dungeons, and after making his escape he continues his journey with [[estellise_sidos_heurassein|Estelle]] and his faithful dog [[Repede (tales)|]] for the sake of the common people. His seiyuu is [[Toriumi Kousuke]] and his English voice actor is [[Troy Baker]] ([[Grant George]] in the Definitive Edition content).

Not to be confused with (and oddly not voiced by) Yuri Lowenthal.

title: natalia_luzu_kimlasca_lanvaldear
body:
The princess of the Kimlasca kingdom in [[Tales of the Abyss]]. Natalia believes in [i]noblesse oblige[/i], always serving her kingdom and interacting with commoners. She does her best to help others, but sometimes acts selfishly. Also known for being an atrocious cook, though given her upbringing, this isn't too surprising.

title: tear_grants
body:
The main heroine of [[Tales of the Abyss]], a 16-year-old soldier working for the Order of Lorelei. She undertakes a personal mission to kill her older brother [[Van Grants]], but accidentally warps herself and [[Luke fon Fabre]] out of the Fabre mansion. Tear helps Luke get back to his home, all while dealing with his bratty behaviour with a cool and harsh demeanor. Her seiyuu is [[Yukana]].

title: luke_fon_fabre
body:
The main hero of [[Tales of the Abyss]], an aristocrat born in Kimlasca who was kidnapped at a young age by the rival empire Malkuth and had his memory erased. He had to relearn everything and has been extremely sheltered for fear of another kidnapping happening. Thus, Luke is spoiled, bratty and very arrogant towards everyone. He gets caught in the world's events when [[Tear Grants]] appears at the manor. His seiyuu is [[Suzuki Chihiro]].

title: ibm
body:
The International Business Machines Corp (IBM) is an American multinational technology corporation that is headquartered  Armonk, New York, with operations in over 171 countries. It was founded in 1911 and produces and sells computer hardware, middleware and software, as well as hosting and consulting services.  They're also a major research organization generating many patents every year.

IBM regularly spins-off or sells their various low margin divisions so they may focus on more profitable markets.  The printer and imaging company Lexmark originated from IBM's former printer manufacturing division.  IBM's personal computer division that produced their [[ThinkPad]] line was sold to Chinese company [[Lenovo]].

h4. External Links

* "Wikipedia - IBM":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IBM]

title: tallgeese_ii
body:
[b]OZ-00MS2 Tallgeese II[/b]
A modification of the [[Tallgeese]] built out of salvaged spare parts. The modernized Tallgeese II was distinguishable by its yellow flared head ornament (as opposed to the original Tallgeese's red one), blue trim, and a Gundam-like face. Other than that, it was functionally the same fearsome MS as its predecessor, with a striking presence on the battlefield - aided by the guile and genius of its pilot [[Treize Khushrenada]].

title: ryuujou_kai_ni_(kancolle)
body:
Ryuujou's Kai Ni form.
Her second remodel gives her a different shirt collar with three magatama hung under, her skirt gains white stripes along the brim, a golden flight deck scroll, with the necklace attached to the scroll and her blue flames are now golden as well.

She has Christmas portraits for her first and second remodels.

Her second portrait (second remodel) gives her the vest, her mini-visor and the ski shoes; adapted for this remodel as well as white pantyhose, tiny present boxes in her sack, a set of cat ears and tail and her flight deck scroll has been redrawn with a christmas tree on the deck and presents where the AA guns should be. With her "Holy Night" flames, she can use her Shikigami plane-sleighs propelled with fireworks and paper reindeer to deliver presents.

title: regal_bryan
body:
One of the nine playable characters of [[Tales of Symphonia]]. Regal was a rich, intelligent young man, and president of the Lezarano Company. But after being forced to kill his fiancee, the despair-ridden Regal convicted himself. When [[Lloyd Irving|Lloyd]] and his party help him tie up this haunting loose end, he joins the party to defeat the ones who tore him apart for his departed love. His shackles are a memento of his past.

He's also an accomplished chef.

h4.Costume Titles

* [[regal bryan (dandy)|Dandy]]
other_names: リーガル・ブライアン

title: presea_combatir
body:
One of the nine playable characters of [[Tales of Symphonia]]. Presea is a silent, emotionless girl [[Lloyd Irving|Lloyd]] and company meet soon after they land in Tethe'alla.  When the group discovers that Presea is the victim of Cruxis Crystal experiments that took away her emotions and froze her growth, Lloyd agrees to make a Key Crest to cancel out the negative effects her Exsphere has on her. After turning back to normal, Presea agrees to help Lloyd's party to make up for the time she has lost. Her seiyuu is [[Kuwashima Houko]].

h4.Costume Titles

title: zelos_wilder
body:
A protagonist from [[Tales of Symphonia]], Zelos is the handsome, carefree Chosen of Tethe'alla. Zelos is appointed by the King of Tethe'alla to keep tabs on [[Lloyd Irving|Lloyd]]'s group while they travel in his homeland. His seiyuu is [[Onosaka Masaya]].

Together with [[Tales of the Abyss]]'s [[Jade Curtiss]], Zelos hosts a series of omakes entitled [i]Viva! Tales of![/i]

h4.Costume Titles

* [[zelos wilder (narcissist)|Narcissist]]
* [[zelos wilder (pickup artist)|Pickup Artist]]

title: lloyd_irving
body:
The main protagonist of [[Tales of Symphonia]]. After being exiled from the village of Iselia, Lloyd set out with [[Genis Sage|Genis]] to find their childhood friend [[Colette Brunel|Colette]], and see her save the world of Slyvarant. After traveling to the parallel world of Tethe'Alla, Lloyd takes up center stage, leading the party's quest to unite the two worlds. His seiyuu is [[Konishi Katsuyuki]].

In the [[Tales of Symphonia Knight of Ratatosk]], Lloyd serves as a heroic antagonist to replacement hero, [[Emil Castagnier|Emil]].

h4.Costume Titles

* [[lloyd irving (arrgh me hearties)|Arrgh Me Hearties]]
* [[lloyd irving (beach boy)|Beach Boy]]
* [[lloyd irving (fang of the white lions)|Fang of the White Lions]]
* [[lloyd irving (nobleman)|Nobleman]]
* [[lloyd irving (unrivaled blade)|Unrivaled Blade]]
other_names: ロイド・アーヴィング

title: raine_sage
body:
A protagonist from [[Tales of Symphonia]], Refill is a half-[[elf]] and [[Genis Sage]]'s older sister. Refill is the professor at Iselia's school, and is [[Lloyd Irving|Lloyd]], [[Colette Brunel|Collet]], and Genius's teacher. The calm and collected "Professor" helps the party with her healing and buffing spells. Just don't let her near any ruins. Or [[bad food|supper]].

Her name in the Japanese version is [b]Refill Sage[/b].

h4.Costume Titles

* [[raine sage (glorious beauty)|Glorious Beauty]]
* [[raine sage (no not the sun!)|No, Not the Sun!]]

title: genis_sage
body:
A protagonist from [[Tales of Symphonia]], Genius is a half-[[elf]] and [[Raine Sage]]'s little brother. Genius follows his best friend and foil [[Lloyd Irving|Lloyd]] after the dual swordsman is banished from Iselia. Genius is a child prodigy, and uses offensive [[magic]] augmented by a [[kendama]].

He also has a huge crush on [[Presea Combatir|Presea]].

h4.Costume Titles

* [[genis sage (beach comber)|Beach Comber]]
* [[genis sage (easter sunday)|Easter Sunday]]

title: colette_brunel
body:
The main heroine of [[Tales of Symphonia]], and [[Lloyd Irving|Lloyd]]'s childhood friend/primary love interest. The Chosen of Mana of the world of Sylvarant, beneath Colette's [[dojikko]] exterior lies a responsible young girl who would go to extremes to make sure her friends do not worry about her. Her seiyuu is [[Mizuki Nana]].

title: arachne
body:
A common variety of monstrous [[spider girl]] in which the human parts beneath the waist/torso have been entirely replaced by the body of a [[spider]]. [[Extra eyes]] are a common addition. Good examples can be found in "Rachnera Arachnera's character sheet":[/posts/1808116] or the "Monster Girl Encyclopedia entry":[/posts/395047].

Note that merely having spider parts (e.g. post #1282030) is not enough for this tag. For spider-legged girls retaining human legs, consider [[arthropod limbs]] and [[extra legs]].

For monster girls of similar body type but not based on spiders, see [[centauroid]].

h4. See also
* [[arachne boy]]

title: aliasing
body:
An image defect that results in jagged or pixelated looking lines.

Aliasing artifacts are mostly caused by the artist resizing the image poorly, or by poor filtering during [[3D]] rendering.

When tagging, judge the image in full resolution, as the browser itself may produce aliasing artifacts when resizing the image. Especially consider the regularity of the undesired pattern and intended art style, as not all [[jaggy lines]] are due to a technical flaw.

This tag is for aliasing artifacts that are an unintended technical flaw. See [[jaggy lines]] for intentional aliasing as part of an art style.

h4. See also

* [[jaggy lines]]
* [[JPEG artifacts]]

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Aliasing":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aliasing]

title: izumo_(masterwork_apocalypse)
body:
Character from [[Masterwork Apocalypse]].

[b]Origin:[/b] Kojiki (古事記, "Records of Ancient Matters" or "An Account of Ancient Matters"), an early Japanese chronicle of myths, legends, hymns, genealogies, oral traditions, and semi-historical accounts down to 641 concerning the origin of the Japanese archipelago, the kami (神), and the Japanese imperial line. It's claimed in its preface to have been composed by Ō no Yasumaro at the request of Empress Genmei in the early 8th century (711–712), and thus is usually considered to be the oldest extant literary work in Japan.

[b]Japanese voice actress:[/b] [[Hara Yumi]].

title: yingning_(masterwork_apocalypse)
body:
Character from [[Masterwork Apocalypse]].

[b]Origin:[/b] Liaozhai zhiyi (Liaozhai; Chinese: 聊齋誌異), known in English as Strange Tales from a Chinese Studio, a Chinese romance fantasy novel. It's a collection of Chinese folk tales by Qing dynasty scholar Pu Songling (蒲松龄). Many of the stories collected have to do with ghosts and fox spirits.

[b]Japanese voice actress:[/b] [[Yukana]].

title: rezi
body:
Artist, digital colorist for visual novels and illustrations.

Has worked in VN studio "Witch":[https://vndb.org/p768] between 1999 and 2005 as CG chief and CG supervision, in VN studio "Miris Pellet":[https://vndb.org/p1533] as CG chief ([[Tutorial Summer]], 2005) and between 2005 and 2018 in VN studio "AXL":[https://vndb.org/p214] as CG chief, all under pseudonym "tetu". He's friends with [[Senomoto Hisashi]] (character designer, artist, founder of AXL). Worked on some graphics (backgrounds and effects) in [[Sorcery Jokers]] VN (2015, available in English). Worked on "Gensou Rougoku no Kaleidoscope (2020)":[https://vndb.org/v25583#main] backgrounds and chibi (SD) characters coloring.

His illustrations were featured in the artbook "100 Masters of Bishoujo Paintings generation 2":[https://www.amazon.co.jp/%E7%B5%B5%E5%B8%AB100%E4%BA%BA-generation2-%E6%9D%91%E7%94%B0%E8%93%AE%E7%88%BE/dp/4861008883] (絵師100人 generation2, 2013). Were also displayed in "pixiv × FIREFLY Illustration Exhibition":[https://times.pixiv.net/post/119270687085/pixivxfirefly] in Guangzhou, China in 2015.

He's been doing coloring for Senomoto Hisashi's doujinshi covers ("Million Bank":[https://www.doujinshi.org/browse/circle/1511/Million-Bank/]) and some monochrome drawings on the last pages. Also drawn covers for Angel's Stroke issue 18 and 28. Has never made any doujinshi or manga.

Has done character designs for Isabella in [[Hortensia Saga]] mobile game (from f4samurai), Miharu Katagiri in [[Shooting Girl]] browser game (from DMM) and for 5 playable girls in [[monster_hunter_mezeporta_kaitaku-ki|Monster Hunter Mezeporta Reclamation]] browser game (from DMM).

Accepts some commissions when the type of work and pay is appropriate. He himself wrote that he also does sketches which don't get posted anywhere. He doesn't post on Twitter as far as we know.

Over the years he deleted or set to private many works on his Pixiv account, but thanks to uploaders they are available on gelbooru, danbooru and other websites.

title: kirishima_kai_ni_(kancolle)
body:
Kirishima's second remodel.
For her second remodeling, she gains the same modifications as Kongou and her rig is replaced with one used by Kongou. She is also noticably taller than her sisters.

title: hiei_kai_ni_(kancolle)
body:
Hiei's two second remodels.

For her second remodeling, she gains the same modifications as Kongou, replacing her spider rig with a ship-like rig, except that the hairband is turned into hairclips (and have a different design) and she has a shorter haircut.

For the 7th anniversary of the game, she was given a Kai Ni C remodel like Kongou's with all the updates and modifications that implies. Her hair also grew somewhat longer than her base form and her hairclips appear to be connected to each other.

title: gotland_andra_(kancolle)
body:
Gotland's second remodel.

For her second remodel she trades her sailor collar and neckerchief for a collared shirt and necktie, and trades her socks for thighhighs. Her landing pad is also replaced with a group of anti-aircraft guns, reflecting her conversion to an AA cruiser in 1944.

title: jun'you_kai_ni_(kancolle)
body:
Jun'you's second remodel.

For her second remodel, she now wears a white and green vest under her blouse, a green sash as well as a new green paint job for her ship parts and platforms. Her hakama is clearly revealed to be trousers (it was partially occluded by her flight deck in her original art). She now uses two scrolls, her actual flight deck and a smaller one, appearing to be her hangar, which can be held in a compartment in her "hull". Both emits purple flames from the sides. Like Ryuujou, she has three magatama but unlike her, the two extra magatama are hanging from earrings instead of being hung under her collar. She also reveals that she can change the text on her flames in her damaged portrait where she uses the character "Forbidden" to self-censor her exposed bra and panties. The level where she can be remodeled as such is Level 80, one of the highest and equal to Haruna.

title: taiyou_kai_ni_(kancolle)
body:
{{taiyou_(kancolle)}}'s second remodel.

In her Kai-Ni form, she wears a grey scarf and headphones with a radio tower on the right side, and her flight deck carries a late-war camouflage pattern.

title: zara_due_(kancolle)
body:
Zara's second remodel.

For her second remodel, she loses the pantyhose and wears a garter on her left thigh, while her skirt becomes layered, with a layer of white underneath the red. She gains a cleavage cutout in her corset, and her boots now have high heels. Her hair now features a side braid on the left side of her face. For her machinery, the positions of her turrets is altered, and she gains additional secondary batteries and anti-aircraft guns. She now wields a seaplane launcher that resembles a Breda 30.

title: fletcher_mk_ii_(kancolle)
body:
With the May 20, 2020 update, Fletcher obtained two reversible remodels: (Kai) Mod.2 and Mk.II.

Mod.2 switches her net for headphones and a quintuple torpedo launcher. Mk.II, her "real" second remodel, modifies her outfit somewhat by giving her tight sleeves, a black skirt and black thighhighs. Her gear has been overhauled and features experimental ASW weapons, including a surface-to-underwater rocket launcher turret mounted on what appears to be a boxy bullpup rifle chassis. Her new equipment reflects the historical destroyer's post-war anti-submarine offense role. She is officially the first non-Japanese destroyer in the game to obtain a second remodel.

title: bismarck_drei_(kancolle)
body: Bismarck is (to date) the only ship-girl in Kancolle's roster with a third remodel which serves more of an actual upgrade rather than a ship class change (like the Chitose-class). Her [i]drei[/i] form gives her the ability to launch torpedoes. This refers to Tirpitz's own modifications which included the addition of torpedo launchers. She never got those modifications, having been sunk in early 1941.

title: inamori_megumi
body: Original character by [[orizen]]. Mother of [[Inamori Futayo|Futayo]] and [[Inamori Chiyoko|Chiyoko]].

title: bukka-chan_(butudan_butugu)
body: An original character by [[Butudan Butugu]]. She was originally created as a Mii, as revealed by the artist "on Twitter":[https://twitter.com/butudan_butugu/status/934316872039673856].

title: ooi_kai_ni_(kancolle)
body:
Ooi's Kai Ni form, differentiable from base and Kai forms by her bared midriff and lighter colored serafuku.

Much like her sister Kitakami, they change to a khaki and dark green uniform that shows their midriff. They now have quintuple torpedo launchers instead of the quad torpedo launchers.

title: saratoga_mk_ii_(kancolle)
body:
Saratoga is the first Allied girl to gain a second remodel (post #2852915).

Her neckwear becomes black with an anchor attached, the skirt part of her white dress gains stripes, and she now wears black fingerless gloves. She also has a Mod.2 form where she switches to a full black dress (post #3226144). In both forms, her flight deck now bears the number 3 and the roundels on the magazines are now also modified to the form the US Air Force currently uses since 1944.

In the game, she also gains the ability to engage in night battle cut-ins, with her Mod.2 form converting her into an armored carrier. This is reflective of her real-life 1944 refit that saw her operate as a night carrier (CV(n)) before damage sustained in Iwo Jima relegated her to a training carrier.

title: kitakami_kai_ni_(kancolle)
body:
Kitakami's K2 form.

Much like her sister Ooi, they change to a khaki and dark green uniform that shows their midriff. They now have quintuple torpedo launchers instead of the quad torpedo launchers.

title: gundam_gp-04_gerbera
body:
[b]RX-78GP04G Gundam "Gerbera"[/b]
The fourth unit of the Gundam Development Project. Intended to act as a high speed assault unit, the Gerbera was equipped with three "Sturm Booster" hybrid fuel tank/thrusters on its back, enabling it to have impressive range and mobility. However, as its role clashed with the [[Gundam GP-01 Zephyranthes]], it was decided to initially move it to a long range fire support type by adding a long beam rifle to the unit before further development of the machine was ended.

[spoiler]The incomplete GP04 would eventually be handed to [[Cima Garahau]] of the Delaz Fleet, having been refitted externally to resemble a more Zeon-like design and rechristened the [[Gerbera Tetra]].[/spoiler]

title: dagon_(housamo)
body:
A [[Tokyo Afterschool Summoners]] character.
Designed by [[bombom]].

Transient from Old Ones who possesses winding, squirming [[tentacles]]. He is also a lecturer at Toyosu Gakuen University and a specialist in ocean construction. His appearance highly resembles a certain teacher at Shinjuku Academy, but the directions they go in are complete opposites. Rather than aim for the greatest heights with someone, he holds strong ruinous desires to sink to the deepest depths of depravity with another. He likes social meeting places for adults, and there is always calming yet decadent pheromones drifting about him. He does not belong to any of the 23 worlds connected to Tokyo, and he has the same name as a certain ancestor from another world. He seems to like his coworker who desires to investigate sunken relics. And above all, as Dagon has little desire for money he is unlikely to get into a dispute over his shares, so they mesh well.

h4. External Links

* "Housamo Wiki: Dagon":[https://housamo.wiki/Dagon]

title: butterfly
body:
A butterfly is any of several groups of mainly day-flying [[bug|insects]] of the order Lepidoptera, the butterflies and [[moth|moths]]. Like other holometabolous insects, butterflies' life cycle consists of four parts, egg, [[larva]], pupa and adult.

Butterflies have large, often brightly coloured [[butterfly_wings|wings]], and conspicuous, fluttering flight.

title: detroit:_become_human
body: A 2018 game published by Quantic Dream released for Playstation and PC. The game is set in 2035, where players control three humanoid androids in the wake of one murdering its owner, sparking a hunt for other "deviant" androids. [[connor_(detroit)|One]] is investigating other deviant androids following the murder in question alongside a [[hank_anderson|human partner]] distrustful of androids, [[kara_(detroit)|another]] has gone deviant and is trying to escape to Canada alongside a young girl after fleeing an abusive owner, and [[markus_(detroit)|a third]] has found itself at the forefront of a budding revolution alongside fellow deviant androids. The player's actions while controlling the characters have an impact on how the course of events in the game go and the ultimate outcome of the android revolution.

title: last_story_wa_anata_e
body:
From "VNDB":[https://vndb.org/v4775]:

[i]"One winter day main character logs in to Hypersense Network's cyber shopping mall to buy new memory. It is the so-called “Cyber Akihabara”. As soon as he punts in his ID and starts walking on the main street, his protocol is hijacked and screen distorts with poisonous colors. This illusion feels like a real Akihabara even though the weight of mouse and just bought memory can be felt in hands. With a lightning strike electronic machine starts to act up, and protagonist finds himself dragged into a dream-like twilight world."[/i]
other_names: ラストストーリーはあなたへ。

title: one_breast_out
body:
When one [[breasts|breast]] is exposed while the other remains covered or confined by clothing. See [[breasts out]] for when both breasts are exposed.

If the exposed breast is only partially exposed, the entire [[nipples|nipple]] and [[areolae|areola]] should be visible.

This tag most often accompanies [[open shirt]], [[wardrobe malfunction]], [[shirt pull]], [[bra pull]], or similar tags, but it is not a necessity.

Remember that just because you cannot see the other unexposed breast, it does not implicitly mean this tag should be used.  The unexposed breast could simply be blocked from view by the persons arm or hand, or the body of another character in the picture.

h4. See also

* [[breasts out]]
* [[Tag Group:Attire]]
* [[Tag Group:Body Parts]]
* [[Tag Group:Breasts Tags]]

title: totoki_airi
body:
An [i][[iDOLMASTER Cinderella Girls|iDOLM@STER Cinderella Girls]][/i] character from the Passion (Yellow Sun) category. She has brown eyes and short brown twintails. She also has considerable curves. Her Nickname is "Totokin".

She appears prone to feeling too warm, leading her to, among other things, strip down out of the blue, without regard for where she may be at the time. Other idols and the Producer try to make sure she keeps her clothes on.

Due to her popularity, she was selected as 2012's Cinderella Girl from a general election held in the game. Following earning that title, she was selected for the third CINDERELLA MASTER CD series, alongside [[Kohinata Miho]], [[Tada Riina]], [[Honda Mio]] and [[Kawashima Mizuki]]. Her seiyuu is [[Harada Hitomi]].

* Age: 18
* Height: 161 cm
* Weight: 46 kg
* Birthday: December 8
* Blood type: O
* Three sizes: 88-58-88
* Hobbies: Baking cakes
* Writing Hand: Right
* Horoscope: Sagittarius
* Hometown: Akita

title: rainbow_cake
body:
A normally multilayered [[cake]], usually around 6 layers, with each layer being a separate color to create a rainbow when put together.  This is most commonly done by using food dye in the batter for each cake layer, but some cakes instead use different colored frostings to distinguish the layers.

Not to be confused with the Italian-American rainbow cookie, a 3-layer sponge cake cookie that traditionally features the colors green, white and red after the Italian flag.

title: kuben_blisk
body:
"Oi. This fight is what you were born for."

A known war criminal of the Frontier, Kuben Blisk operates the mercenary group known as the Apex Predators, a group commonly employed by the IMC. He displays a passive outlook on war: so long as he gets his pay, he doesn't care what side he's fighting on.

He also is the organizer of the Apex Games in [[Apex Legends]], appearing in game's initial launch trailer and several other supplementary materials including in-game loading screens, comics, and [[Rampart (apex legends)|]] and [[Valkyrie (apex legends)|]]'s Stories from the Outlands shorts.

title: stereogram
body: A stereogram is an optical illusion of depth created from flat, two-dimensional image or images. Originally, stereogram referred to a pair of stereo images which could be viewed using stereoscope or by crossing one's eyes and focussing on the resultant phantom image that appears between the two real ones. Other types of stereograms include [[anaglyph]]s and autostereograms.

title: charisma_establishment
body:
The opposite of [[charisma break]]. When a character suddenly turns very stoic / charismatic / cool from a less formal state.

h4. Guidelines 

* No meta-knowledge about the character should be required to enjoy the humour.
* The change must be dramatic, not subtle. 
* The change must occur within the same image as consequential event (expression charts or similar images do not count).

h4. See also

* [[charisma break]]

title: piyo_piyo_(phrase)
body: An onomatopoetic Japanese phrase piyo piyo suru {ピヨピヨする} which means to make a chirping or cheeping sound. A sound you would normally expect from a chickidee. It is roughly translatable to the "spring of adolescence", where people are carefree and happy-go-lucky. The most familiar use of this phrase is the [[piyo_piyo_apron]] worn by [[Otonashi_Kyouko]], one of the main characters from [[Maison_Ikkoku]]. It is believed by fans of the series to symbolize some kind of immaturity or refusal to move on in life.

title: scho-ka-kola
body:
A German brand of bitter-sweet dark chocolate known for its strong caffeine and kola nut mix, thus its name: [b]Scho[/b]kolade (chocolate), [b]Ka[/b]ffee (coffee), [b]Kola[/b]nuss (kola nut). The chocolate is divided into wedges held in a round metal canister. The red and white container design and recipe has changed very little since the original launch in 1936.

It was introduced at the 1936 Summer Olympic Games in Berlin as a performance-enhancing energy "Sport Chocolate" ([i]Sportschokolade[/i]).

During [[World War II]], it was also known as "Aviator Chocolate" ([i]Fliegerschokolade[/i]) since it was commonly provided with [[Luftwaffe]] pilot and crew rations, and was also issued to flight crews in blue canisters as emergency sea-survival rations ([i]Seenotpackung[/i]). It was also issued to German tank crews, U-boat crews, and the German Army.

Today, it is sold in Germany in both its original dark chocolate in a red-and-white container as well as a milk chocolate version in a blue-and-white container.

(Note that the term [i]Fliegerschokolade[/i] and its land-based equivalent, [i]Panzerschokolade[/i], were [i]also[/i] widely used by German soldiers and airmen as sarcastic euphemisms for Pervitin brand methamphetamine tablets, which were readily available and heavily used in the German armed forces in the early years of the war.)

See also: "Wikipedia article":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scho-Ka-Kola

title: okazaki_ritsuko
body:
Singer-songwriter (December 29, 1959 - May 5, 2004) famous and beloved for her work on anime music.

She performed the opening and ending themes for [[Fruits Basket]], [[Princess Tutu]] and [[Sukitte Ii Na Yo.]], and wrote "A Happy Life" for [[Gakuen Utopia Manabi Straight!]]. She was also involved in composing music for various series like [[Mahou no Princess Minky Momo]], [[Ai Tenshi Densetsu Wedding Peach]], [[Love Hina]], and [[UFO Princess Valkyrie]]. Her work on [[Symphonic Rain]] was released posthumously.

title: the_refreshing_trio:_alola_idols
body:
[i]The Refreshing Trio: Alola Idols[/i] (サンサン3人はアローラドリンキュン, "W-W-We Three Are Alola DrinKyun"), also known as [i]Thrist-Three[/i] (サンドリ, "SanDri"), is show within a show in the [i][[Pokemon SM (anime)|Pokémon Sun and Moon]][/i] anime. It is a [[magical girl]] series aired by Alola TV and is a reference to [i][[PreCure]][/i] and [i][[Ai Tenshi Densetsu Wedding Peach]][/i], the latter, like the [i][[Pokemon (anime)|Pokémon]][/i] anime, was animated by OLM.

[i]Alola Idols[/i] is featured in episode 113, where the kids visit the Alola TV studios and the girls fill in for the lead actresses when the stars are unable to arrive to the studio in time.

The Alola Idols, unnamed in the English dub, are:
* Tea DrinKyun (ティードリンキュン) ([[Mallow (pokemon)|]])
* Soda DrinKyun (ソーダドリンキュン) ([[Lillie (pokemon)|]])
* Juice DrinKyun (ジュースドリンキュン) ([[Lana (pokemon)|]])

h4. See also

* post #3448139: Transformation sequence.

h4. External links

* "Bulbapedia: SM113":[https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/SM113]

title: gokusai_kaibi
body:
A character introduced in [[Toaru Majutsu no Index]], and featured in the sidestory Toaru Majutsu no Index SS: Biohacker Arc.

For a long time only known as the Girl in the Dress (ドレスの少女) or Measure Heart, she is a teenage girl who participates in [[prostitution|compensated dating]] for money. She is an operative of SCHOOL, acquainted with the ways of the Dark Side of Academy City, and the second of the three Gokusai sisters.

She has [[medium hair|medium length]] [[blonde hair|blonde]] [[wavy hair]] styled in a [[ponytail]] and [[brown eyes]]. She usually wears a [[pink dress|pink]] or [[red dress|red]] [[sleeveless dress|sleeveless]] [[frilled dress|frilled]] [[dress]], leaving her shoulders [[bare shoulders|bare]] along with [[necklace]]s and [[bracelet]]s and [[white footwear|white]] [[sandals]]. She often has an [[expressionless]] disposition.

She has the ability "Measure Heart (心理定規)" which lets her regulate "the distance between people's hearts," making them feel closer or more distant to a person despite what their memories and reason say otherwise.

title: nobel_gundam
body:
[b]GF13-050NSW Nobel Gundam[/b]
The mobile fighter of Neo Sweden in [[G Gundam]], piloted by [[Allenby Beardsley]]. Notable for it's feminine appearance, highlighted by it's [[long hair|long]] [[blonde hair]] and serafuku-inspired design, leading to many comparisons to [[Sailor Moon]]. The unit is equipped with a Berserker System, which increases it's output while sending the pilot into an uncontrollable rage. It was renamed to [b]Noble Gundam[/b] in the English dub.

In both the original TV series and many of it's [[Super Robot Wars]] and [[SD Gundam G-Generation]] appearances, it's been capable of performing a [[Bakunetsu God Finger]]. In the manga adaptation, it is succeeded by the [[Super Nobel Gundam]] for the final battle.

When Jack is jealous, he'll take an extra step to get rid of what he's jealous of or at least satisfy himself by doing what he thinks is best to be better than the person/thing that is better than him.

title: vesves_(sailor_moon)
body:
The red-haired character from the manga and anime [[Bishoujo Senshi Sailor Moon]] (aka. Pretty Soldier Sailor Moon) by [[Takeuchi Naoko]]. Known as the Magician of Beasts of the Dead Moon Circus, and former antagonist of the Inner Sailor Senshi.

During the series she a part of the Amazon Quartet and fourth youngest sister (in the anime she is the second-oldest). Later in the manga she is revealed to be [[Sailor Vesta]] who protects [[Chibi Usa]].

Voiced by Hagimori Junko in the 1990s anime, and [[Takahashi Rie]] in Crystal.

title: if_you_draw_heart-shaped_pupils_this_will_become_a_nsfw_image_(meme)
body:
A Twitter [[meme]] inspired by a tweet by [[Fukai Ryosuke]].

Original tweet (now deleted):

[quote]
かわいい女の子絵の瞳にハートを描きこんだら「それは成人向けの表現なので控えて」というチェックが返って来たがソレは先入観ではないのかーーっっ！

I added [[heart-shaped_pupils|hearts in cute girl's pupils]] in my art and received a correction request: "You're better off without that because it represents NSFW art." [i]BUT ISN'T THAT PREJUDICE!?[/i]
[/quote]

[[Shikio Satoru]]'s "response":https://twitter.com/str_dorobou/status/647273106017382401

[quote]
ここはタグを作るべきではないだろうか #瞳にハートを描きこむと成人向けの絵になる

It's time to create a Twitter hashtag, isn't it? #If-You-Draw-Hearts-in-the Pupils-This-Will-Become-a-NSFW-Image
[/quote]

title: ruger_super_redhawk
body: A double-action revolver line introduced by Sturm, Ruger and Company in 1987. The Super Redhawk is a large, heavily built revolver, usually long-barreled and visually identifiable by its distinctive frame, which extends for some distance along the barrel in front of the cylinder to support an integrated mounting system for a telescopic sight. Originally available only in .44 Magnum, it has since been offered in other large-bore cartridges, such as .454 Casull and .480 Ruger, as well as 10mm Auto. It is only made in stainless steel.
